  "system": {
    "description": "<p>The caster utters a one-word directive, which the subject or subjects, up to one creature for every 2 levels, obeys to the best of their ability unless they make a charisma saving throw. The command must be clear and understood by the targeted creature. A command of \"die\" causes the subject to fall unconscious for the duration of the spell, whereas a command of \"suicide\" would fail because it is generally used as a noun, not as a command. A command of \"awake\" will counter magically induced unconsciousness caused by <em>sleep</em> and <em>color spray</em>.</p>",
